original: Lindholm, Nils Torsten Natanael, teol. o. fil. kand., kyrkoherde, Tenge-ne, f. 9/12/91 i Floby, Skarab. 1. G. 31 rn. Birgit Gustavsson. Barn: Gunnar f. 34, Göran 38. — Stud:ex. i Gävle 10, fil. kand. 12, teol. kand. 15, prakt. teol. prov s. à. Tjg. i Kinne-ved, Eriksberg, Österplana, kommin. i Ransberg 18, i Lidköp. 20, las :pred. 20, kyrkoh. i Tengene fr. 25. Miss :’Styr. stiftsomb. 30, ordf. i kyrkostämma o. skolråd. Skr.: Minnen fr. helgedomen I o. II, Från gångna sabbatsstunder I o. II, Huru Jesus hjälper en männ. fram t. en lev. tro, Vården om vår själs hälsa, Den hel. tjänsten, Andens nya liv.
translated:
Lindholm, Nils Torsten Natanael, theology and philosophy candidate, parish priest, Tenge-ne, born on December 9, 1891 in Floby, Skaraborg. Married on May 31st to Birgit Gustavsson. Children: Gunnar, born in 1934 and Göran, born in 1938. 

Education: Graduated from high school in Gävle in 1910, obtained a Bachelor's degree in Philosophy in 1912, Bachelor's degree in Theology in 1915, and completed practical theological examinations. 

Work experience: Served in the parishes of Kinne-ved, Eriksberg, and Österplana. Became assistant clergyman in Ransberg in 1918 and in Lidköping in 1920. Ordained preacher in 1920 and appointed parish priest in Tengene from 1925 onwards. 

Notable positions: Member of the Board of the Diocesan Commission since 1930, chairman of the Church Assembly and School Council. 

Publications: Memories from the Sanctuary I and II, From Past Sabbath Moments I and II, How Jesus Helps a Person Towards a Living Faith, Taking Care of Our Soul’s Health, The Holy Service, The Spirit's New Life.
